  <h1>Skill Wiki documentation</h1>
  <p style="font-size: var(--t-md); color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 70ch;">
    Skill Wiki is a protocol for AI knowledge: <strong>typed atoms with a declared
    edge graph, retrieved on demand</strong>. This site documents the protocol,
    explains why it exists, and walks through the v0.1.0 reference implementation.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you came here from the marketing landing, this is where the actual content
    lives. The site is organised in four kinds of pages:
